<item>
            <title>[LU-10835] dm-flakey module is left loaded</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10835</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The recent landing in master of the patch &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-684&quot; title=&quot;replace dev_rdonly kernel patch with dm-flakey&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-684&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-684&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: replace dev_read_only patch with dm-flakey&quot; adds a &apos;modprobe dm-flakey&apos; command to test-framework.sh.  There is no corresponding rmmod of this kernel module anywhere.  This leaves the kernel module always loaded, even when it stops being referenced or used by anything.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe remove of the module needs to be added in relevant places like test-framework.sh and lustre_rmmod.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
